One of the suspects was reported to be Sodje's brother Akpo, 33, who plays for Tranmere Rovers.

The League One club said: 'Tranmere Rovers Football Club are aware of Sunday newspaper allegations regarding Akpo Sodje.

'As this is an ongoing investigation, the club will make no further comment at this time.'

Responding
to the claims about Sam Sodje yesterday, Portsmouth FC spokesman Colin 
Farmery said: 'If these serious allegations are true, then we are 
extremely shocked and saddened by them, as match-fixing of any type goes
to the heart of the integrity of the game.

'The
player in question no longer plays for the club and we have not been 
contacted by the authorities, but of course we would co-operate fully 
with any inquiry.'

